{
  "stem": "12289.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a big section for those, what we called, safeguarding of the other countries' interests, their citizens, who were, perhaps, left behind, their buildings and so on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was a big job in the Swedish Foreign Office during the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a big department in Stockholm heading this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at-- at every embassy in-- where the-- the country was in war, had a section to do-- to deal with those questions.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Could you please describe a very ordinary day of your life during that time?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Do you went to the office in the morning and what happened?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, of course, I did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and I tried then to-- to-- to help Raoul Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was the-- of course, how could you supply these houses with food and all that?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was also a big organization, too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We sent people out in the countryside to buy on the black market, to buy-- to buy-- to buy food, also with the help of American money, to supply and medicine and all that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Imagine, they-- they lived in these houses to start with 5,000 people and perhaps then we, in all secrecy, we increased that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So towards the end of the war, when we assessed this situation, we found that at least around 20,000 people were living there, and with the Swedish protective passports, and were all saved, more or less.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my job was to give him, give Wallenberg some advice and so on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was always discussions, between him and me, how far can we go?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We have now illegally given not only 5,000 but perhaps, slowly, for 20,000 people passports and so on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How far can we go?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We can certainly not give the whole population protective passports, because then it will lose its value.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
